# MacPaint image data
# Created by Apple for the original Macintosh, 1984.
# 576x720 monochrome bitmap, PackBits compressed.
# Three variants:
#   1. MacBinary: 128-byte MacBinary header + 512-byte paint header + data
#      (PNTGMPNT at offset 65 — already detected by Magdir/apple)
#   2. Version header: 4-byte version (2 or 3) + 304 bytes brush/pattern
#      data + 204 bytes reserved + pixel data
#   3. Null header: 512 bytes of zeros + pixel data
# PRONOM: x-fmt/161
# Netpbm: macptopbm, pbmtomacp

# MacBinary variant (already in Magdir/apple line 778)
# 65	string	PNTGMPNT	MacPaint image data

# Version 2 with default brush patterns
0	belong		0x00000002
>4	belong		0xFFFFFFFF	MacPaint image data, version 2
!:mime	image/x-macpaint
!:ext	mac/macp/pntg

# Version 3 with default brush patterns
0	belong		0x00000003
>4	belong		0xFFFFFFFF	MacPaint image data, version 3
!:mime	image/x-macpaint
!:ext	mac/macp/pntg
